A class template is prescription for creating a class in which one or more types or values are prameterized .
Let us see how to define and declare class templates  template &lt;class T&gt;

template key word always begins both the definition and a declaration of a class template .
template key word is followed by list of user defined data type separated by comma
and surrounded by the less than (&lt;) and greater than (&gt;) tokens.
In place of class key word typename could also be used as shown below template &lt;typename T&gt;

Below is the simple program to understand the template class
#include &lt;iostream&gt;
using namespace std;

template &lt;class ValueType&gt;
class tempClass
{
public:
tempClass(){}
void updateDataType(ValueType data);

};

template &lt;class ValueType&gt;
void tempClass &lt; ValueType&gt;::updateDataType(ValueType data)
{
 cout &lt;&lt;"data="&lt;&lt;data&lt;&lt;endl;
}
int main()
{
    tempClass&lt;int&gt; tempObject;
    tempObject.updateDataType(5);

    tempClass&lt;char&gt; tempObjectchar;
    char value='a';
    tempObject.updateDataType(value);
    return 0;
}
template class can also have nontype parameter ,mostly it will be constant template &lt;class T, int size&gt;
